very emphatic ending.

00:12:36.100 --> 00:12:42.340
And then in 111 it seems to just
rise above to a different sphere.

00:12:42.340 --> 00:12:45.150
So, I suppose these last three
sonatas you get these three

00:12:45.150 --> 00:12:48.600
different types of
resolving, of resolution.

00:12:48.600 --> 00:12:52.600
&gt;&gt; DAVID PLYLAR: And maybe a good
example of Schubert's feeling

00:12:52.600 --> 00:12:55.050
like it could be going on to
a different thing is it sort

00:12:55.050 --> 00:12:58.830
of circular feeling that a major
sonata, where when it comes back

00:12:58.830 --> 00:13:02.300
to that material, that
feeling of the beginning,

00:13:02.300 --> 00:13:03.600
at the very end of the book.

00:13:03.600 --> 00:13:04.900
&gt;&gt; PAUL LEWIS: Yeah.

00:13:04.900 --> 00:13:06.470
&gt;&gt; DAVID PLYLAR: It almost feels
